1
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:08,733
<i>You still have feelings for her,
don't you?</i>

2
00:00:08,867 --> 00:00:10,933
<i>Don't twist my helping Marj
into something else.</i>

3
00:00:11,067 --> 00:00:12,700
<i>You know what?
Your mind is so dirty.</i>

4
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,067
<i> Do you even care</i>

5
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,900
<i>- about our child?
- Marj, I already explained</i>

6
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:16,900
<i> to you everything.</i>

7
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> Then why do I feel like this?</i>

8
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>Why does it feel like
you just left me hanging?</i>

9
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,767
<i>I'm going back
to Torrecampo Realty.</i>

10
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:24,867
<i> I will never beg Paolo</i>

11
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,467
<i>to take you back
into his company.</i>

12
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>They'll be the ones kneeling
and begging me to come back.</i>

13
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:32,200
<i>I need you to do
something for me.</i>

14
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> And if you do as I say,</i>

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>no one will ever find out
what you did to me.</i>

16
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:39,033
<i>I can't believe
you convinced Mr. Lorenzo</i>

17
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:42,000
<i>not to pull out his investment.</i>

18
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:45,233
<i>That's why I want her back
immediately.</i>

19
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:48,767
But Dad...

20
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,167
I think that's a terrible idea.

21
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,967
I mean, I'm grateful
for Thea's help,

22
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:57,867
but that doesn't mean
we need to hire her back.

23
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,133
She's the only one who solved
our problem.

24
00:01:02,267 --> 00:01:06,533
It only proves that she's
indispensable to the company.

25
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:12,000
If there's anyone
who's being ridiculous,

26
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,167
it's you.

27
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,367
But Dad, you know where I'm
coming from, right?

28
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:19,767
Dad.

29
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,500
What is it, Paolo?

30
00:01:22,267 --> 00:01:23,233
What's the problem?

31
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:27,600
Are you afraid that
if we work together again,

32
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:30,067
you'll be tempted again by me?

33
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:33,567
Come on.

34
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,633
We've been living together
under one roof.

35
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:38,867
And there hasn't been any
problem, right?

36
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,033
Is that what you're afraid of?

37
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:44,533
Why is that still an issue?

38
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:48,833
Haven't you learned anything
from your mistakes before?

39
00:01:48,967 --> 00:01:51,800
Oh, I already learned my lesson.

40
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,900
I'm not so sure about your son.

41
00:01:58,533 --> 00:01:59,867
I love Marj.

42
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,333
And I have no intention
of cheating on her again.

43
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:05,367
Well then.

44
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,800
That settles it.

45
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:10,000
Set aside 'yung issue niyo
with each other

46
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:12,300
and prioritize
the company's welfare.

47
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:17,533
I want Thea reinstated starting
tomorrow.

48
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,767
Is that clear, Paolo?

49
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,233
Yes, Dad.

50
00:03:19,133 --> 00:03:21,333
Oh, one brewed coffee, please.

51
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:22,400
Black.

52
00:03:22,533 --> 00:03:23,500
Thank you.

53
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:26,400
Mr. Edward Torrecampo.

54
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:28,633
Yes?

55
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:29,800
I knew it was you.

56
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:33,233
By the way,
I'm Francisco Matias.

57
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,500
And...

58
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,900
I'm from Vallejo Realty.

59
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,433
Vallejo Realty?

60
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:47,667
What are you doing
approaching me?

61
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,400
Isn't your company the rival
of our family business?

62
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:51,500
That's right.

63
00:03:51,633 --> 00:03:53,367
We used to be number one.

64
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:56,900
Until Torrecampo Realty
came into the picture.

65
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,800
Leave me out of it.

66
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,400
I've been out of the company
for a long time.

67
00:04:02,533 --> 00:04:04,667
I know. that's exactly why
I approached you.

68
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:08,633
we have a very good proposal
for you.ou're interested,

69
00:04:09,267 --> 00:04:11,933
I'm sorry, but don't you think
it's unethical for me

70
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:14,933
to do business with my family's
rival company?

71
00:04:15,067 --> 00:04:17,067
Please, think about it.

72
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:21,067
Give that number a call
after you do.

73
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:22,767
Excuse me.

74
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,467
Brewed coffe, Sir.

75
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,100
Thank you.

76
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:41,033
<i>I want to consult to you
regarding Paolo, Mom.</i>

77
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:43,133
<i> Marj, sweetheart.</i>

78
00:04:43,267 --> 00:04:45,767
I understand how you feel.

79
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:51,867
Of course, you hoped Paolo
would never leave you.

80
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,167
And he would always be
by your side.

81
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,700
But you know, Marj,

82
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,033
I understand Paolo, too.

83
00:04:57,967 --> 00:04:59,733
Really?

84
00:04:59,867 --> 00:05:03,033
He can't split himself in two.

85
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:08,733
Maybe he chose to be away more
often and work

86
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:12,100
to provide for Jasmine's needs.

87
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:15,567
But even if you don't see each
other often...

88
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:21,267
I'm sure Paolo is still taking
good care of you.

89
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,967
Marj, he's making sacrifices.

90
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:27,133
Not just for your family,

91
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:29,400
but for the Torrecampo family
as well.

92
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:33,333
<i>Remember, even before he made
promises to you,</i>

93
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:35,333
he was already bound
to his responsibilities

94
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,267
to his family.

95
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:40,567
<i>So, my dear, Paolo is carrying
a heavy burden too.</i>

96
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,667
Maybe you're right, Mom.

97
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,300
I guess I forgot about that.

98
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:49,833
<i> I didn't even thank him</i>

99
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,567
<i> for saving Jobert.</i>

100
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:53,500
For covering his mistake
at work.

101
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:56,500
I really appreciate that, Mom.

102
00:05:57,633 --> 00:06:00,200
I just let my frustration get
the better of me.

103
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:03,500
Marj, maybe you should give him
some space for now.

104
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:10,267
Marj, use this time apart to
understand each other better.

105
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,500
<i> Before you talk again.</i>

106
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,300
Okay, Mom.

107
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:18,633
Thank you.

108
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,300
Excuse me.

109
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,633
Where's Jasmine Torrecampo's
room?

110
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:25,967
Let me check.

111
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,633
It's room 401.

112
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,500
Okay, thank you.

113
00:06:30,633 --> 00:06:31,767
Xander?

114
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:35,600
Ah...

115
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:38,067
Are you Jasmine's mom?

116
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:42,700
Are you visiting
a relative here?

117
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:45,633
Not exactly, Auntie.

118
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,267
I'm here to see Jasmine po.

119
00:06:51,467 --> 00:06:52,933
That's sweet, hijo.

120
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:54,767
I'm sure Jasmine would
appreciate it,

121
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,833
but she can't have visitors
right now.

122
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,733
That's too bad.

123
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:02,333
We even skipped summer class
just to come here, Auntie.

124
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:08,067
Jasmine's immune system
is still very sensitive.

125
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:11,167
You can come back
once she's better.

126
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,500
Well, your charm didn't work.

127
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,367
Weak.

128
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,667
You're a weak?

129
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,000
Please, Auntie.

130
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:22,367
Just five minutes.

131
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,267
I already said no.

132
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,367
And please don't call me
"auntie."

133
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:30,300
Because you're not my nephew.

134
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,933
You have to understand,
Attorney.

135
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,867
I'm not used to losing a case.

136
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:42,533
Talk to whoever
you need to talk to

137
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:44,067
and do whatever it takes.

138
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,633
- Thank you.
- Yes, Sir.

139
00:07:45,767 --> 00:07:47,733
- Have a nice day.
- Thank you, take care.

140
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:53,700
Evelyn?

141
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:57,933
What are you doing here?

142
00:07:58,067 --> 00:08:00,367
I'm picking up Jobert.

143
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:05,333
Next time you come here...

144
00:08:06,267 --> 00:08:11,300
at least fix yourself up and
dress nicely.

145
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:17,800
You think I can still do that?

146
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,933
Dress up?

147
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:22,233
With all the problems
my family has?

148
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:25,500
Especially now that Jasmine
is sick?

149
00:08:25,633 --> 00:08:27,533
We're not the same.

150
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,167
You can still make yourself
look good

151
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,433
because you don't even care
about our grandchild.

152
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,933
Did you just say I'm handsome?

153
00:08:38,067 --> 00:08:41,133
That's not what I meant.

154
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:43,867
I know.

155
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,267
I'm just teasing you.

156
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:47,367
Ah...

157
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,567
You know, Evelyn...

158
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:53,967
ah, just because
I carry myself well,

159
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:58,433
doesn't mean I'm not concerned
about Jasmine.

160
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,800
I just don't want
to face our grandchild

161
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:03,167
looking like I'm full of
problems.

162
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,000
She might end up
worrying even more.

163
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:12,600
So if I were you...

164
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:14,967
I'd fix myself up.

165
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:17,800
So you don't look older than 70.

166
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:20,933
Hey! I'm only 60!

167
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,033
You, rude man.

168
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:34,367
What a rude man, no manners.

169
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:37,900
Calling me 70 when I'm only 60.

170
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,300
Hi, Sir.

171
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:41,833
Hello.

172
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:51,567
Ah, wait! Hold! Hold!

173
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:52,733
Please! Please!

174
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:14,100
Thanks for agreeing to let me
come back here.

175
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:17,867
Let me make this clear.

176
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:24,500
I only agreed because of Dad.

177
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:25,933
That's the only reason.

178
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:28,500
But I don't want trouble.

179
00:10:28,633 --> 00:10:31,967
So if possible, while we're here
in the office,

180
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,067
let's just stay out of each
other's way.

181
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:02,733
It's kind of cold
in this elevator.

182
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,133
But why do you look like...

183
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:07,433
you're sweating?

184
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:24,433
Ah, excuse me, excuse me.

185
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,600
How rude.

186
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:41,400
He thinks so highly of himself
just because he's rich.

187
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:43,567
Please, he's not even handsome.

188
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:44,833
Honestly...

189
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:46,200
What am I supposed to do?

190
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,500
Go to a salon first before
coming here?

191
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:49,067
Just to pick up my kid?

192
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:53,000
Mom, why are you mad?
Who are you fighting with?

193
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,100
Who else?

194
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:56,067
Your sister's arrogant
father-in-law.

195
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,167
Who does he think he is to look
down on people like that?

196
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,867
His mouth just keeps
insulting me.

197
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,333
Just because he's wearing
expensive clothes,

198
00:12:03,467 --> 00:12:05,833
he thinks everyone else is
trash?

199
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:07,067
Is he all tough and impressive?

200
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,467
His skin's already all wrinkled.

201
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,033
Who does he think he is?

202
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:16,767
Last time I checked, my skin was
still soft.

203
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,333
Not wrinkled.

204
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:25,333
Has he been here the whole time?

205
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:27,233
Yes.

206
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:30,433
Did he hear everything
I said, son?

207
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:32,133
Yes.

208
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:37,667
Greg, I'm sorry, okay?

209
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,900
I haven't even had lunch yet.

210
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,367
Sorry, Greg.

211
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,567
It's all right.

212
00:12:43,133 --> 00:12:44,700
There you go...

213
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:47,033
that's better.

214
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,567
See? It suits you.

215
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,267
She said it suits you, Mom.

216
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,433
You look good, Mom.

217
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:31,367
Jas, I hope you're okay.

218
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,333
Who are you?

219
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:48,400
Ah...

220
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:52,333
I'm Xander, Jasmine's friend.

221
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,300
Xander?

222
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,133
Oh, from her birthday party,
right?

223
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:04,400
Yes, the party.

224
00:14:04,533 --> 00:14:06,200
I saw you there, too.

225
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:07,667
I didn't get your name though.

226
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,367
Ah, I'm Ashley.

227
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:16,133
I'm her cousin
nd also her best friend.

228
00:14:17,033 --> 00:14:19,033
What are you doing here?

229
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,333
Jas is in the hospital.

230
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:22,700
I know.

231
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:25,567
Jasmine's mom won't let us get
near her.

232
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:29,333
So, I decided to drop by
and give this.

233
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:31,667
Ah, I see.

234
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:37,567
My Aunt Marj won't let me
visit either.

235
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:39,967
She said maybe later when...

236
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:42,167
- Jasmine's condition improves.
- Jasmine's condition improves.

237
00:14:43,733 --> 00:14:44,800
What's that?

238
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:49,500
That's exactly
what she said to me.

239
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:55,033
I guess I'll just give this to
her once I'm allowed to visit.

240
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:56,233
See you.

241
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:57,400
Do you miss her?

242
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,867
Of course.

243
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,967
We're not just cousins...

244
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,033
we're BFFs.

245
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,033
So, how about this?

246
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,967
Let's visit Jasmine...

247
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:21,233
in secret.

248
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:23,800
Huh?

249
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:25,567
So, you wanted to see her,
right?

250
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:26,800
I wanted to see her.

251
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:30,567
So let's sneak in
and visit Jasmine.

252
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:31,633
What do you think?

253
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:33,233
Let's plan it.

254
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:42,800
Thank you, Sir Greg asked me

255
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:44,567
to forward this to HR

256
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,533
so you can report tomorrow.

257
00:15:46,967 --> 00:15:47,867
Great!

258
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,200
I'll head back right away.

259
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:50,567
Thank you.

260
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:10,033
I think it's a little too late
for you to avoid me.

261
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:13,533
I noticed earlier...

262
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:20,433
how you kept staring at my
cleavage.

263
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,300
Don't you feel guilty doing
that?

264
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,933
I know you did it on purpose.

265
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:33,767
Why would I feel guilty?

266
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:36,367
Edward's doing
his own mischief, too.

267
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,367
What are you talking about?

268
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:43,433
I know he's not over Marj yet.

269
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:45,067
What?

270
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,700
Come on.

271
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:48,967
Do you really think
he's completely moved on

272
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:51,767
and has zero feelings left
for Marj?

273
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:53,467
That was a long time ago.

274
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:57,033
I guess he was just that serious
about Marj before.

275
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:59,933
That's probably why he still has
feelings for her.

276
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:04,167
And you're okay with that?

277
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:06,400
That your husband is in love
with another woman?

278
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:10,467
Well, that's just how men are.

279
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:12,800
I already expected that kind
of nonsense from you, guys.

280
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,833
Even from Edward.

281
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:21,000
And don't you like that?

282
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:25,000
If something actually happens
between him and Marj...

283
00:17:25,467 --> 00:17:27,567
then you and your wife
would be even.

284
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:37,033
Marj isn't that kind of woman.

285
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,533
She's not like you.

286
00:17:51,967 --> 00:17:53,967
You've done more than enough,
Edward.

287
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:57,033
You don't have
to come visit every day.

288
00:17:57,167 --> 00:18:00,733
Thea might get mad if you keep
showing up here all the time.

289
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,600
Why would she get mad?

290
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,133
I'm not doing anything wrong.

291
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:08,933
I'm just bringing you dinner

292
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:12,267
because I know you're not eating
properly.

293
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,733
And I'm keeping an eye on you
to make sure

294
00:18:14,867 --> 00:18:15,800
you actually eat it.

295
00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:16,900
You're so dramatic.

296
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:18,500
Is it really that bad
if I don't feel hungry?

297
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,867
Oh, so now I'm the dramatic one?

298
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:25,833
Fine, I'm the dramatic one.

299
00:18:25,967 --> 00:18:27,800
But thanks for the concern.

300
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:33,800
I'm just saying, Marj...

301
00:18:34,267 --> 00:18:36,067
I want you to take care
of yourself.

302
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,733
Of course,
I'm taking care of myself.

303
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:42,400
Jasmine needs me.

304
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:43,967
I can't afford to get sick.

305
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,167
It's a good thing you're here.

306
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:49,767
It's a big relief knowing
my daughter and I

307
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,167
have extra support.

308
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,500
Of course.

309
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:57,133
Because, Marj...

310
00:18:57,267 --> 00:19:00,367
I know what it feels like
to have no one beside you.

311
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,600
You know, when my business
in Cebu shut down...

312
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:06,433
I hit rock bottom.

313
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:10,900
I had no one to turn to,
no one to talk to.

314
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,167
I failed.

315
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,333
Not even Thea.

316
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:15,867
Especially not Thea.

317
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:18,967
Honestly, I almost lost hope
back then.

318
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:23,967
So believe me when I say
I understand how you feel

319
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:27,333
when it seems like
you're all alone.

320
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,567
Ah...

321
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:32,200
I know I'm not alone.

322
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:34,533
The whole family is there.

323
00:19:35,167 --> 00:19:36,633
Paolo's there, too.

324
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:42,067
But you know the feeling?

325
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,867
He's there, but he's not really
there.

326
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,100
Sometimes I just don't
understand Paolo.

327
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,967
I don't approve of him
prioritizing

328
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:58,300
his work problems over you
and Jasmine.

329
00:19:58,433 --> 00:20:01,233
Because as the head
of the family,

330
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,533
he should always be present.

331
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:05,100
You're supposed to draw strength
from him.

332
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,100
Edward!

333
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:17,067
You talk as if you understand
what I'm going through!

334
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,067
- Paolo!
- Are you...

335
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,433
Are you the one poisoning
my wife's mind

336
00:20:21,567 --> 00:20:24,233
so she'll always be
mad at me? Huh?

337
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,167
Answer me!

338
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:31,933
What, you want to hurt me?
Choke me? Go ahead.

339
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,967
Come on, do it, go ahead.

340
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:40,000
Paolo, what are you doing?

341
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:43,833
Paolo, stop it!
This is embarrassing!

342
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:44,900
What's wrong with you?

343
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,300
You barely come here,

344
00:20:46,433 --> 00:20:48,367
and now you're just looking
for a fight!

345
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:52,733
Why are you even taking this
idiot's side?

346
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,500
Get out of here!

347
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:57,967
Edward isn't doing
anything wrong, Paolo.

348
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,900
He's the one helping me here,

349
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:01,867
and he's the one who called
the best doctors

350
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,067
for Jasmine, so don't tell him
to leave!

351
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,867
Fine! Then I'll be the one
to leave!

352
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,233
Then I'll be the one
to leave!

353
00:21:09,133 --> 00:21:11,000
It's not like you need me here
anyway

354
00:21:11,133 --> 00:21:12,867
since my oh-so-great brother
is already here!

355
00:21:13,433 --> 00:21:14,667
You two can stay together!

356
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:17,000
Paolo, wait! Paolo!

357
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,933
Marj?

358
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,833
Thanks.

359
00:22:28,867 --> 00:22:31,900
Paolo still isn't answering
any of my calls.

360
00:22:33,467 --> 00:22:37,700
The last time he did this was
when he and Thea got stranded.

361
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:39,300
Remember?

362
00:22:41,233 --> 00:22:44,167
My husband is really
furious with me.

363
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:47,867
I'm sorry.

364
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:51,967
I think I'm the reason you
and Paolo are fighting.

365
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,233
I shouldn't have said that
about him.

366
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,900
He's right anyway.

367
00:22:58,667 --> 00:23:01,367
I'll never really understand

368
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,500
what he's going through.

369
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:08,833
But Edward, that doesn't change
the fact

370
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:10,833
that you're here for me.

371
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:14,600
I'm forever grateful.

372
00:23:17,033 --> 00:23:18,400
Marj?

373
00:23:21,167 --> 00:23:23,000
Do you remember the promise
I made to you before?

374
00:23:24,567 --> 00:23:26,433
Back when Paolo wasn't
in your life yet?

375
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:30,000
<i>I'm serious about my feelings
for you.</i>

376
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:31,767
<i> I'll take care of you.</i>

377
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:33,800
<i> I'll never abandon you.</i>

378
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,933
That hasn't changed.

379
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:40,433
I still care for you.

380
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,200
A lot.

381
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:20,867
Looks like you need some help.

382
00:24:33,467 --> 00:24:34,300
Excuse me.

383
00:24:34,433 --> 00:24:35,500
Move aside, Thea.

384
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:43,633
Didn't I already tell you to
stop bothering me?

385
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:45,967
If you don't leave, I will.

386
00:24:46,533 --> 00:24:48,100
Relax.

387
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:51,400
You don't have to avoid me.

388
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:54,567
Your wife isn't here anyway.

389
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:58,267
She's probably with my husband
right now.

390
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,333
- No.
- What's the matter?

391
00:25:21,467 --> 00:25:22,800
You can't make me do this again.

392
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,400
Paolo!

393
00:25:25,533 --> 00:25:27,500
Let me have it, please!

394
00:25:27,633 --> 00:25:28,867
Off, please.

395
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:30,800
Hey!

396
00:25:30,933 --> 00:25:32,300
Get back here!

397
00:26:06,133 --> 00:26:09,800
Jasmine's body is rejecting her
current medications.

398
00:26:10,333 --> 00:26:11,600
she

399
00:26:13,533 --> 00:26:15,433
I think we need to consider

400
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:18,033
that experimental treatment
in Hong Kong.

401
00:26:18,167 --> 00:26:20,167
Think about it again,
Mrs. Torrecampo.

402
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:21,533
Experimental treatment?

403
00:26:21,667 --> 00:26:22,533
Hong Kong?

404
00:26:22,667 --> 00:26:24,567
If it's experimental,

405
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:27,600
that means there's a risk
to Jasmine's condition.

406
00:26:27,733 --> 00:26:28,733
It's dangerous.

407
00:26:28,867 --> 00:26:30,733
Our daughter could die
because of that.

408
00:26:30,867 --> 00:26:32,400
And I don't want to gamble
with her life.

409
00:26:32,533 --> 00:26:34,500
That's exactly what happened
to the company.

410
00:26:34,633 --> 00:26:36,933
I can't stand seeing my daughter
suffer anymore.

411
00:26:37,067 --> 00:26:39,567
Maybe I should really bring her
to Hong Kong.

412
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,933
But doesn't Paolo object to
that?

413
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,533
Let him get mad if he wants.

414
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:46,867
What matters
is my daughter's life.

415
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:49,833
The board has decided
to hire someone

416
00:26:49,967 --> 00:26:53,100
to work exclusively on the
project.

417
00:26:53,233 --> 00:26:56,900
Everyone,
this is Aldrin Castelo,

418
00:26:57,033 --> 00:27:01,467
the Menagerie Manor Project's
new Sales Director.

419
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:02,567
Good afternoon, everyone.

420
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:05,667
I'm Aldrin Castelo of
Castelo Prime Holdings.
